erformance across runs. We evaluate RaSFAR on benchmark datasets including ANLI, FewRel, and a clinical diagnostic corpus, comparing against strong baselines such as RDL, standard ERM, and data augmentation via back-translation. We expect RaSFAR to outperform all in OOD accuracy (+5–8%) and exhibit lower variance across few-shot splits (<0.5% std vs >2% in baselines), demonstrating its potential as a scalable, human-effort-minimizing method for robust few-shot learning.",
